107
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,260
but Lee Jun is...

108
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,640
from a free show years ago.

109
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,390
Hey, sir.

110
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:44,500
I admire you so much. What can I say?

111
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,430
Oh, really.

112
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:49,130
What are you saying? It's your turn.

113
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:50,720
Oh, really?

114
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:53,200
We have done a good job, so...

115
00:05:57,660 --> 00:05:58,650
I've finished mine.

116
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:01,830
Not bad.

117
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,620
I'll drink until I'm drunk.

118
00:06:04,620 --> 00:06:06,490
Really? Have one more cup then.

119
00:06:06,490 --> 00:06:07,460
Hey,

120
00:06:08,030 --> 00:06:09,860
you shouldn't drink so quickly.

121
00:06:10,190 --> 00:06:12,620
Yes, she is right.

122
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:14,130
General Manager,

123
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:20,140
you are totally different from him.

124
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:23,590
How?

125
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,720
The General Manager

126
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:30,220
is pretty tough,

127
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,800
while Lee Jun is...

128
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,370
soft.

129
00:06:37,850 --> 00:06:40,030
It is true.

130
00:06:40,770 --> 00:06:41,710
Soft.

131
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:43,780
Actually I'm also a bit tough.

132
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:47,670
Yes, you are right.

133
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:50,670
Starting all over is not
something everyone can do.

134
00:06:51,850 --> 00:06:53,200
Ah, starting all over.

135
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:56,910
You are talking about
his remarriage, right?

136
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:00,270
Oh, no.

137
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:02,610
Ah, it turns out

138
00:07:02,790 --> 00:07:04,730
you also started all over, right?

139
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,070
Let's drink to that.

140
00:07:07,340 --> 00:07:10,440
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

141
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:15,340
Fighting.

142
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,560
- That's OK.
- Fighting.

143
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,400
Thank you.

144
00:07:18,590 --> 00:07:19,430
Are you all right?

145
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,000
You are not
very uncomfortable, are you?

146
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,160
I'm fine.

147
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:26,950
I'll drink some chocolate milk later.

148
00:07:30,140 --> 00:07:31,210
Here, chocolate milk.

149
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:34,250
It'll make me feel better.

150
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:36,690
Just leave the table,

151
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:38,010
and come back after finishing it.

152
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:41,360
Thank you.

153
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:42,840
Just go.

154
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:06,860
Cheers.

155
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,530
Wow.

156
00:08:10,220 --> 00:08:12,770
Good one. Very good.

157
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,400
- Thank you.
- Good one.

158
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:18,500
- Would you like another one?
- OK, of course.

159
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,160
- Sir.
- Yeah.

160
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,550
- Thank you.
- I should thank you.

161
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:24,640
You know what?

162
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:25,710
You can do it.

163
00:08:25,710 --> 00:08:27,770
Doesn't matter. You can do it.

164
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:29,040
Really?

165
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:30,380
Let's drink to it.

166
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:37,150
It's the first time
I've seen you drink soju.

167
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,140
This is rare.

168
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:44,240
This rare soju

169
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:51,990
is soft.

170
00:08:54,550 --> 00:08:55,600
General Manager.

171
00:08:59,410 --> 00:09:01,510
Hey, are you OK?

172
00:09:01,770 --> 00:09:03,160
Yes.

173
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:05,030
I need a designated driver.

174
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:08,890
Oh, I feel cold.

175
00:09:23,820 --> 00:09:24,660
Where are you going?

176
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,640
Where else can I go?

177
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:30,870
Have fun at another place?

178
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,160
Home.

179
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,480
Are you taking a taxi?

180
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:41,270
No, I'll take the bus.

181
00:09:42,910 --> 00:09:45,370
Alright, goodbye, General Manager.

182
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,120
Be careful on the road.

183
00:09:50,110 --> 00:09:50,950
You are not leaving?

184
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:54,220
I am.

185
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:57,420
Take care, Lee Jun.

186
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:09,880
Ah...

187
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:13,680
Didn't you just say you would be free?

188
00:10:25,610 --> 00:10:29,220
Ah, my first day of work is finally over.

189
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:35,990
Ah... Oh...

190
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,170
(Mom)
Son, you must be busy on your first day,

191
00:10:49,170 --> 00:10:50,650
so I'm just sending you a message.

192
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:53,840
I sent you your favorite Ganjang Gejang.

193
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,880
Remember to eat it.

194
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:58,740
You'll break my heart
if you work hungrily.

195
00:10:58,740 --> 00:10:59,580
Ha!

196
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:03,150
You think I'm a little boy?

197
00:11:13,170 --> 00:11:15,490
Ah, the smell of alcohol.

198
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:20,240
What happened to him?

199
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:22,270
He's totally grown up.

200
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:34,820
Today was like as long as a month.

201
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,570
Ah! This is not my shirt.

202
00:11:56,010 --> 00:11:56,850
Oh...

203
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,700
It stinks with the smell of alcohol.

204
00:11:58,930 --> 00:11:59,770
I should put it in water.

205
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,560
Isn't this good?

206
00:12:08,610 --> 00:12:10,570
You need someone
to take care of you,

207
00:12:10,570 --> 00:12:11,530
and I can do that.

208
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:14,000
And you'll have my smell on you.

209
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:19,550
It smells really good.

210
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,890
There's no smell of alcohol at all.

211
00:12:26,890 --> 00:12:28,060
I should give it back to him like this.

212
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:30,930
No, I can't.

213
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:35,020
A tooth for a tooth,
and an eye for an eye.

214
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:39,510
So I should repay kindness
with kindness.

215
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:49,500
Wow, it's been such a long time.

216
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:51,040
It reminds me of the old days.

217
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:54,070
I did this a lot
when I was a trainee idol.

218
00:12:59,170 --> 00:13:00,080
Hm?

219
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:02,430
Who would come here so late?

220
00:13:04,860 --> 00:13:05,770
Ah!

221
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,120
Maybe it's the Ganjang Gejang!

222
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:13,020
Ganjang Gejang! Ganjang Gejang!

223
00:13:15,260 --> 00:13:17,030
Huh? Choi Jun?

224
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:26,180
Why did you open the door
without asking who it is?

225
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,080
That is not safe.

226
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:30,440
My agent said the same thing.

227
00:13:32,530 --> 00:13:33,390
Your agent?

228
00:13:34,070 --> 00:13:35,400
No, I mean...

229
00:13:36,170 --> 00:13:39,180
You shouldn't have come
without asking me.

230
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,700
Hey.

231
00:13:49,660 --> 00:13:51,240
Hey, how do you know I live here?

232
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,540
This time, I don't want to lose...

233
00:14:01,230 --> 00:14:03,450
I don't want to miss it,
so I've been watching,

234
00:14:04,780 --> 00:14:05,620
and watching.

235
00:14:06,140 --> 00:14:06,980
What?

236
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:10,280
Seoul City...

237
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:18,090
Ah... Oh...

238
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:21,150
You shouldn't have drunk so much.

239
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:25,280
It's a secret I was born with.

240
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:31,800
You know my secret anyway.

241
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:34,920
Do you want me

242
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,080
to tell you another secret?

243
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:41,870
No need.

244
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:45,680
Hey! Hey! Hey!

245
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:48,350
You know what?

246
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,760
I'm very drunk now.

247
00:15:00,380 --> 00:15:01,900
- What?
- Ha-ha-ha...

248
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:09,200
You call that a secret?

249
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,780
Is that a secret?

250
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:15,780
Hey, get up.

251
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:18,000
Hey!

252
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:22,240
Get up now.

253
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:25,230
Unbelievable.

254
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:36,700
Yeah, that's right.

255
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:41,460
Your arm.

256
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:48,209
♪It weighs on your shoulders♪

257
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:52,100
♪like a heavy luggage♪

258
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:55,100
You call this American style?

259
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,430
I think it's Korean style.

260
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:58,350
I'll help you anyway.

261
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:02,540
♪Where am I going for you♪

262
00:16:03,610 --> 00:16:05,210
